{"TopicId":193505,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Ground radar","CreatedByName":"RedAlex","CreatedById":204346,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-30T22:49:03Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"RedAlex","CreatedById":204346,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-30T22:49:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGround radar,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne of the problems with landing is that you dont know the level of the terrain, unfortunaly not al celestial bodies have nice flat spots at sealevel like Minmus.\u003Cbr\u003E\nSo an usefull and realistic solution can be the use of a groundradar. As a seperate part that can, ore not, be used by builders choice. If used it should give a indication of how far away touchdown is.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGreat game by the way, but i guess i dont need to tell that to the people here..:)\u003Cbr\u003E\nGreetings from the Netherlands to all Kerbals and all who fly them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlex\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tonka Crash","CreatedById":189552,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-01T00:19:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n@RedAlex have you tried SCANsat? You can map planets from orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u002257416\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed7786401395\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/72679-180-scansat-v1814-real-scanning-real-science-at-warp-speed-october-28-2019/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:211px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr the\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RoninFrog","CreatedById":203049,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-01T03:12:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nClick on the water icon next to the altitude gauge.\u00A0 Is that what you are wanting?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-05-01T03:12:14Z\u0022 title=\u002205/01/2020 03:12  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMay 1, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by RoninFrog\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RedAlex","CreatedById":204346,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-01T13:35:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nill check\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pds314","CreatedById":70014,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-05T05:43:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHasn\u0027t a ground altimeter been in the cockpit view since like 2013? And now there\u0027s one in the main view if you just toggle it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-05-05T05:44:18Z\u0022 title=\u002205/05/2020 05:44  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMay 5, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Pds314\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}